The wreckage of the vehicle involved in the accident on the Total-Kericho Road. [Kipsang Joseph, Standard]  Five people were killed and seven others were admitted to hospital after a 14-seater matatu burst its tyres in Londiani.  Those injured in the accident at Jubat on the Total-Kericho road are admitted at Londiani Subcounty Hospital, Londiani OCPD Joseph Mutungi said.  He added that the occupants had hired the matatu to ferry them from Nakuru to Kisumu.  One of the victims said the accident was caused by a tyre burst. [Kipsang Joseph, Standard]  Man pours hot tea on wife's private parts for reading his messages  Careless lorry drivers and narrow bridges that claim innocent lives  Our son's killers will never know peace, say slain student's family  Lorry driver involved in accident that killed six yet to be found At Londiani Subcounty hospital, Michael Bright is admitted with fractures sustained during the accident.  He said he has with his brother in the vehicle boarded in Nakuru.  "We were on the way to Kisumu for a road trip. On reaching the accident scene, I heard the sound of a tyre burst. The next thing I knew the vehicle was flipping and rolling," Bright said.  He added, "At this moment, I have not seen him. I am not aware of his whereabouts."      Ajali ya Londiani: Abiria watano wafariki kwenye ajali, matatu ilipasuka gurudumu ikiwa kasi  Abiria wanne wafariki katika ajali ya barabarani katika eneo la Murang'a  Interview with Transport PS Irungu Nyakera on the increasing number of deaths from road accidents By Kennedy Gachuhi | 6 hours ago By Winfrey Owino | 7 hours ago By Winfrey Owino | 10 hours ago By Stephen Rutto | 10 hours ago